{"text": "As seen from the plot, the average velocity of the car between time t = 5 s and t = 7 s is : 
Geometrically, this is the slope of the straight line P1P2 connecting the initial position P1 to the final position P2  as shown in Fig.", "fibs": ["plot"]}
{"text": "The average velocity can be positive or negative depending upon the sign of the displacement.", "fibs": ["velocity"]}
{"text": "It is zero if the displacement is zero.", "fibs": ["displacement"]}
{"text": "Fig.", "fibs": ["Fig"]}
