{"text": "Since velocity is a quantity having both magnitude and direction, a change in velocity may involve either or both of these factors.", "fibs": ["velocity"]}
{"text": "Acceleration, therefore, may result from a change in speed (magnitude), a change in direction or changes in both.", "fibs": ["Acceleration"]}
