{"text": "An interesting feature of a velocity-time graph for any moving object is that the area under the curve represents the displacement over a given time interval.", "fibs": ["feature"]}
{"text": "A general proof of this statement requires use of calculus.", "fibs": ["proof"]}
{"text": "We can, however, see that it is true for the simple case of an object moving with constant velocity u.", "fibs": ["case"]}
