{"text": "3.11 Area under v–t curve equals displacement of the object over a given time interval.", "fibs": ["v–t"]}
{"text": "The v-t curve is a straight line parallel to the time axis and the area under it between t = 0 and t = T is the area of the rectangle of height u and base T. Therefore, area = u × T = uT which is the displacement in this time interval.", "fibs": ["curve"]}
{"text": "How come in this case an area is equal to a distance?", "fibs": ["case"]}
